  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Line a deep baking tray (we used a 20cm x 20cm tray) with parchment."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To a bowl, add the almond butter, ¾ of the maple syrup, ½ the almond extract and a pinch of flaky salt. Mix until combined then set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a separate bowl, mash the banana with a fork until smooth. Add the remaining maple syrup and almond extract along with the oats, protein powder, almond milk, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda and a pinch of flaky salt. Stir to combine then fold through the raspberries."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour ½ the banana oat mix into the prepared baking tray then drizzle over ½ the almond butter mix, then top with the rest of the oat mixture and repeat with the almond butter mix before scattering over the flaked almonds."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slide the tray into the oven to bake for 45 mins. Keep an eye on it – if the top is getting too dark, cover with tin foil and continue to bake."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Remove from the oven and let it cool before dusting with icing sugar and cutting into pieces. Serve it up in bowls with a dollop of yoghurt and some berry coulis or extra berries, if you like."
    }
  ],
